dc_description_s: Cartographic Details: Scale [1:769,944]. Map of the Coromandel coast in India (i.e. its lower eastern coast) extending from Paliacate [i.e. Pulicat on Pulicat Lake] in the north to Nega-Patnam [i.e. Nagapattinam] in the south. Rivers, roads and tracks are shown between cities and towns. Relief is shown pictorially. Plates 22-23 from: Atlas de d'Anville / Jean d'Anville. [Paris : chez Mr. Demanne ... maison de la Bibliotheque Nationale ..., approximately 1786]. Text in French.|97.5 x 48 centimeters, on sheets 56 x 82.5 centimeters|Scale [1:769,944]|Ames Library of South Asia Maps
